Nginx DEMO use cases :




Case 1 - Load balancing:
------------------------
-------------------------
example:
upstream myServers {
  server backend1 weight=5 max_fails=10 fail_timeout=90s;
  server backend2 weight=3 max_fails=4 fail_timeout=60s;
  server backend3 weight=4 max_fails=2 fail_timeout=30s;
}

- weight
- max_fails
- fail_timeout


upstream backend {
	server backend1.com max_conns=300;
	server backend2.example.com;
  queue 100 timeout=90;
}

upstream myServers {
	hash $request_uri

	server backend1.com;
	server backend2.com;
	server backend3.com;
}



OSS : RR,IP-HASH,HASH,LC 
+ : least_time and random 

Example: 
- least_time 


Steps : 
conf:
upstream myServers {
	least_time header;

		server backend1.com;
		server backend2.com;
		server backend3.com;
}
- random 
conf:
upstream backend {
    random two; least_time=last_byte;
    server backend1.com;
    server backend2.com;
    server backend3.com;
    server backend4.com;
}


Case 2 DB and API setup;
------------------------
------------------------

Info :
- api directive enable
- zone directive (upstream context)
- status_zone (server context) 

API documentation;
Swagger UI:  https://demo.nginx.com/swagger-ui/
Things you can do with the api:
	get version
	get list of endpoints
	get list of SSL statistics / reset SSL stats
	get status of server memory zones
	get status of upstream server groups
	add/delete a server to/from an upstream server group
	get the sync status of a node

conf: API directive
-------------------

server {
    listen 8080;
    location /api {
        api;write=on;
        allow 192.168.0.0/16;
        deny all;
    }
}

conf : Zone directive 
---------------------

upstream myServers {
    zone backend 64k;
    server backend1 weight=1;
    server backend2 weight=3;
    state /etc/nginx/conf.d/backend.state;
}

conf: Status directive:
-----------------------

server {
    listen 8081;
    root /server/backend1;
    status_zone us;
}
server {
    listen 8082;
    root /server/backend2;
    status_zone apac;
}

conf : Dash board directive 
server { 
    listen 8080;
    location /api {
        api;
    }
    location /dashboard.html {
        root /usr/share/nginx/html;
    }
}

Curl :
curl -X GET "http://localhost/api/5/http/upstreams/myServers/servers/" -H "accept: application/json" | jq

State file for permance:
upstream myServers {
    zone backend 64k;
    server backend1 weight=1;
    server backend2 weight=3;
    state /etc/nginx/conf.d/backend.state;
}

Case3 Session persistence:
--------------------------
--------------------------

Sticky cookie
-------------

upstream backend {
    server backend1.example.com;
    server backend2.example.com;
    sticky cookie srv_id expires=1h domain=.example.com path=/;
}

Sticky route
------------
upstream backend {
   server backend1.example.com;
   server backend2.example.com;
   sticky learn
       create=$upstream_cookie_examplecookie
       lookup=$cookie_examplecookie
       zone=client_sessions:1m
       timeout=1h;
}

Sticky learn
------------
sticky learn
       create=$upstream_cookie_examplecookie
       lookup=$cookie_examplecookie
       zone=client_sessions:1m
       timeout=1h
       sync;
}

case 4 Limiting number of connections:
--------------------------------------
--------------------------------------

upstream backend {
    server backend1.example.com max_conns=3;
    server backend2.example.com;
    queue 100 timeout=70;
}

Health Check
------------

server {
    location / {
        proxy_pass http://backend;
        health_check;
    }
}



http {
    upstream backend {
        zone backend 64k;
        server backend1.example.com;
        server backend2.example.com;
        server backend3.example.com;
        server backend4.example.com;
    }
}

server {
    location / {
        proxy_pass   http://backend;
        health_check port=8080;
    }
}
location / {
    proxy_pass http://backend;
    health_check interval=10 fails=3 passes=2;
}


